OL,6,FThe amended motion criticised
OL,7,FConservative MSP Annie Wells for her
OL,8,F"public pronouncements" on Mr Matheson
OL,9,Fahead of his actions being considered
OL,10,Fby Holyrood's Standards, Procedures
OL,11,Fand Public Appointments Committee ` of
OL,12,Fwhich she is a member.
OL,14,FIt went on to state this "runs the
OL,15,Frisk of the committee report being
OL,16,Fopen to bias and prejudice and the
OL,17,Fcomplaint being prejudged", as it said
OL,18,Fthere should be an independent review
OL,19,Fof the Parliament's complaints
OL,20,Fprocesses.
