OL,6,FIn scenes Scottish Tory leader Douglas
OL,7,FRoss said were "bizarre in the
OL,8,Fextreme", the SNP voted for the
OL,9,Famendment, but then abstained when it
OL,10,Fcame to voting on the amended motion.
OL,12,FMr Ross said while Mr Matheson is now
OL,13,Ffacing suspension and a loss of wages,
OL,14,F"any other Scot would have been handed
OL,15,Ftheir P45 straight away".
OL,17,FHe said: "If someone is found to have
OL,18,Ffalsely claimed #11,000 from their
OL,19,Femployer, in this case the taxpayer,
OL,20,Fthen they lied about it as part of a
OL,21,Fcover-up, they would have been sacked."
